description:
So, you&rsquo;ve decided to return&hellip; and this time you come.. somewhat prepared. With artifacts lending you powers... But there&rsquo;s also new challenges ahead. Traces of faery dust around the land, and new places rearranging the world&hellip; Whirlwinds, sacred trees, moon paths... and not to forget, new powerful master spells to learn.... Are you sure you&rsquo;re ready?

The Forces of Nature expansion for Betwixt and Between includes new powerful artifacts giving each Mystic a magic boost at the start of the game and a special ability to use throughout the game.

The expansion also includes more Exploration Cards with new adventurous places to visit with new actions for your Mystic to put to use to create epic turns!

There are also new challenging master spells to learn for big amount of points, rewarding being smart and creative when building your Magic Weave.&nbsp;

Our Mystics will also find magical Faery Dust sprinkled around the game board, presenting a brand new resource to collect and score points from in different ways!&nbsp;

&mdash;description from the publisher

Fuego! is a race to get rid of all your cards! 
In this game of shifting alliances, players are encouraged to openly plot against each other to prevent opponents from playing all of their cards!

But, beware! When you are about to go out, the other players will try to stop you! Deliberate, strategize and cooperate before &ldquo;Ya Burnt!&rdquo;

It started a long time ago. Apparently, when someone planted a mine in the middle of the yard. Or when someone broke a neighbor's fence&hellip;

Players take turns moving cards or using the properties of one of their cards and destroying opponents' cards. When no one can make a move, the game ends and the one with the lowest sum of lost cards' prices wins.

&mdash;description from the designer

More Surprises Fluxx Expansion

Fans have been asking for a way to add the fun of Surprises to Fluxx decks that don&rsquo;t have this newer type of card, and now you finally can! The ten cards in this pack can be added to any version of Fluxx (even one that already has Surprises, since More Surprises just means even more fun). Includes the original 4 Surprise cards, several that are uncommon, and a couple that are totally new, like Double Draw and (No) Free Lunch! And remember &mdash; a Surprise can also cancel another Surprise, which can also be canceled by another Surprise, etc&hellip;

Publisher's blurb

The Singaporean Dream: The New Normal is the latest edition of The Singaporean Dream, an interactive card game that lets you pay, steal, and sabo your way to be the perfect Singaporean.

You play a classic Singaporean Personality (different for each player) that grants you special powers.

The game goal is to collect as many dream as you can before the dream pile runs out. You can buy the Dream Cards with Cash Cards in the bank or gain them with Action Cards.

During your turn, you draw two cards and play up to 3 actions:

     play an action card from your hand; 
     place money in bank (cards from hand to table);
     buy a dream using money in bank;
     use personality special power.


Keep doing this until the dreams runs out.

The card game adaptation of the 1886 McLoughlin Brothers board game District Messenger Boy.

Each player is dealt cards forming a face down pile. In turn order, players turn over the top card of the pile.  The initial objective is to obtain employment as the Messenger Boy. Over the course of the game players try to advance to more senior positions in the Company, until one player becomes its President.

From the McLoughlin Brothers 1914 Catalogue - &ldquo;The Messenger Boy game has been a favorite for a generation, and there is no evident reason why a card game on the same lines should not be equally popular.&rdquo;
